# Contributing to RestaurantOS

Thank you for your interest in contributing! 🎉  
RestaurantOS is open source and welcomes contributions from everyone.

---

## 🛠 Getting Started

### 1. Fork & Clone
```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/restaurant-ms.git
cd restaurant-ms
npm install
```

### 2. Set up Firebase (for Google Sign-In)
```bash
cp .env.example .env.local
# Fill in your Firebase credentials in .env.local
```

### 3. Run locally
```bash
npm start
# Opens at http://localhost:3000
```

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
src/
├── firebase.js              # Firebase config & Google auth
├── context/AppContext.jsx   # Global state + localStorage
├── pages/
│   ├── AuthPage.jsx         # Login (Google + email/password)
│   ├── Dashboard.jsx        # Stats & charts
│   ├── POS.jsx              # Point of sale + print
│   ├── Tables.jsx           # Table management
│   ├── Kitchen.jsx          # Kitchen display system
│   ├── Menu.jsx             # Menu CRUD
│   ├── Reports.jsx          # Reports with print
│   ├── Staff.jsx            # Staff & role management
│   └── Misc.jsx             # Inventory, Expenses, Reservations, Settings
├── components/
│   ├── Sidebar.jsx          # Navigation
│   └── Notifications.jsx    # Toast system
└── styles/global.css        # Design system
```

---

## 🤝 How to Contribute

### Reporting Bugs
- Open an issue with the bug label
- Include steps to reproduce, expected vs actual behavior
- Screenshots help!

### Suggesting Features
- Open an issue with the enhancement label
- Describe the use case and why it would help restaurant owners

### Submitting a Pull Request
1. Fork the repo
2. Create a branch: `git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name`
3. Make your changes
4. Test locally with `npm start`
5. Build to verify: `npm run build`
6. Push and open a Pull Request

---

## 💡 Ideas for Contributions

- [ ] Dark/light theme toggle
- [ ] Multi-language support (Hindi, Marathi, etc.)
- [ ] Firebase Firestore for multi-device data sync
- [ ] Customer-facing QR menu page
- [ ] WhatsApp/SMS order notifications
- [ ] Staff attendance & shift tracking
- [ ] Customer loyalty/points system
- [ ] Discount & coupon system
- [ ] Split bill feature
- [ ] Export reports to PDF/Excel
- [ ] Mobile app (React Native)

---

## 📋 Code Style

- Use functional React components with hooks
- Keep components focused — one page per file
- Use CSS variables from `global.css` for colors
- All data persistence via `localStorage` (for now)
- Keep the dark theme consistent

